My wife and I ate here after reading the high reviews and were REALLY disappointed.
We visited on a rainy day and they had buckets all over the restaurant to catch water from the leaking roof, and the bathroom was even worse.
I've seen cleaner dive bar bathrooms.
Serious.
Aside from the buckets and bathroom, the food was mediocre at BEST.
The sauces tasted like they came out of a can and the egg drop soup was terrible!
We won't be back.

This restaurant is now closed.

